comment:
* Abstract base class for Connectivity Diagnostics callbacks. Used for notifications about
     * network connectivity events. Must be extended by applications wanting notifications.

methods.name: public void onConnectivityReportAvailable(@NonNull ConnectivityReport report)
methods.comment:
* Called when the platform completes a data connectivity check. This will also be invoked * immediately upon registration for each network matching the request with the latest * report, if a report has already been generated for that network. * *

The Network specified in the ConnectivityReport may not be active any more when this * method is invoked. * * @param report The ConnectivityReport containing information about a connectivity check

methods.name: public void onDataStallSuspected(@NonNull DataStallReport report)
methods.comment:
* Called when the platform suspects a data stall on some Network. * *

The Network specified in the DataStallReport may not be active any more when this * method is invoked. * * @param report The DataStallReport containing information about the suspected data stall

methods.name: public void onNetworkConnectivityReported(@NonNull Network network, boolean hasConnectivity)
methods.comment:
* Called when any app reports connectivity to the System.
         *
         * @param network The Network for which connectivity has been reported
         * @param hasConnectivity The connectivity reported to the System

methodNames: public void onNetworkConnectivityReported(@NonNull Network network, boolean hasConnectivity)
